Returns consistent color classes for project badges.

```javascript
getProjectBadgeClass(projectName) {
  // Return Tailwind classes for project badge based on project name
  // Use a hash to get consistent colors for same project
  const hash = projectName.split('').reduce((acc, char) => {
    return char.charCodeAt(0) + ((acc << 5) - acc);
  }, 0);

  const colors = [
    'bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/30 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-300',
    'bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300',
    'bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/30 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300',
    'bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/30 text-pink-700 dark:text-pink-300',
    'bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900/30 text-yellow-700 dark:text-yellow-300',
    'bg-indigo-100 dark:bg-indigo-900/30 text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300',
  ];

  return colors[Math.abs(hash) % colors.length];
}
```

Hash Algorithm:
```javascript
const hash = projectName.split('').reduce((acc, char) => {
  return char.charCodeAt(0) + ((acc << 5) - acc);
}, 0);
```

This is djb2 hash variant:
1. Start with accumulator = 0
2. For each character:
   - Get ASCII code (charCodeAt)
   - Shift accumulator left 5 bits (acc << 5)
   - Subtract original accumulator (- acc)
   - Add character code
3. Result: Numeric hash

Example:
```javascript
"backend"
  → 'b'.charCodeAt(0) = 98
  → 'a'.charCodeAt(0) = 97
  → 'c'.charCodeAt(0) = 99
  → ... hash computation ...
  → hash = 1234567 (example)
```

Color Selection:
```javascript
colors[Math.abs(hash) % colors.length]
```
- Math.abs(): Ensure positive number
- % colors.length: Modulo gives index 0-5
- Always returns same color for same project name

Examples:
```javascript
getProjectBadgeClass("backend-service")
// → hash = 1234567
// → 1234567 % 6 = 1
// → colors[1] = "bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300"

getProjectBadgeClass("backend-service")  // Same call
// → Always returns green (consistent)

getProjectBadgeClass("frontend-app")
// → hash = 9876543
// → 9876543 % 6 = 3
// → colors[3] = "bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/30 text-pink-700 dark:text-pink-300"
```

Why Hash Instead of Random:
- Random would give different colors on each render
- Hash ensures same project = same color always
- Helps users visually identify projects quickly

